<br>
If you lurk at our board at all, you know that we would never tell someone in mourning that their beloved is worm food. That's not how it works.<br>
<br>
It's just that we grieve with the absence of a belief that everything is all right on the other side, and that there's something more. It's loss without a net.<br>
<br>
That's a big difference, in my opinion, from pretending that &quot;they're not gone, they're just sleeping&quot;, or that the loved one is merely &quot;somewhere else&quot; away from those that love them.<br>
<br>
Jessica<br>
