But, oh...the temptation (Oh, wait - not my point<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
I have to admit leading up to my step-dad's funeral after he was killed a few months ago, I had to wonder how my brother was going to handle the service.  (He's a minister in a very conservative church, unlike me, the pentecostal rebel!)  While we had no idea of Larry's final moments before his death, we both knew that he did not live the life of a Christian, nor did he ever profess to be.  So how would my brother conduct a funeral service that would comfort my mother and yet he could not lie about the very real possibility of where we (he and I) believed Larry to be...<br>
<br>
He spoke of Larry's character, the man that he was for the 13 years that we knew him.   More specifically my brother related his character to the Fruit of the Spirit in Galatians...I was impressed!  Most funerals I've been to have been all wishy-washy with false hopes given as to the eternal resting place of the deceased.  My brother chose to not touch on this aspect at all.<br>
<br>
Okay, digressing from original topic here.  But I wanted to clarify that I don't think you're all a bunch of cold, heartless people...I guess just trying to figure out what <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>you</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> thought would've been more appropriate for Bush to say.  I had no problems for the most part, obviously.   <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Live your life so the preacher won't have to lie at your funeral.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaia25>Gaia25</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#3333ff>(2/3/03 3:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re: Re: Re: Bush</span><hr size=1> I don't think there was any need for him to speak about where they are now, full stop.  He gave his condolences, spoke about how tragic it was etc.  that was enough - he didn't need to say anymore IMO.<br>
